Kaggle Kernel - New York Times Comment - Sentiment Analysis

1. NLTK library

- nltk tokenizer: tokenize words, return a list of words
- nltk stop words: remove rather meaningless words

2. Apply function

- when perform some functions on a dataframe or series, could use apply
- For dataframe or more than one column df[['a','b']], the apply function applies on the SERIES
df.apply(func, axis=0) - apply on each column
df.apply(func, axis=1) - apply on each row

- For dataframe of ONLY ONE column, or a series df['a'], apply function applies on EACH element
